The rise in obesity among Chinese city dwellers is alarming, with 70 million affected due to improved living standards.
Surveys in Shanghai and Beijing reveal high obesity rates, especially in males.
Lack of exercise and poor diet contribute to weight gain.
In Kuwait, hypnotherapy shows promise in treating obesity, linked to psychological issues.
Meanwhile, Kuwaiti women face chronic ailments due to sedentary lifestyles and high-fat diets.
Globally, diabetes cases are set to double by 2025, driven by unhealthy diets and aging populations.
Poor eating habits also plague Hong Kong children, emphasizing the need for healthier choices to combat obesity and related diseases.
